| Pack | Why It Applies | Required Source Targets | Evidence Commands | Result |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| {{CURRENCY_PACK}} | {{WHY_APPLIES}} | {{SOURCE_TARGETS}} | {{COMMANDS}} | {{RESULT}} |

## Required Checks

- runtime support window or LTS status
- package manager and lockfile discipline
- exact app dependency versions or lockfile-backed ranges
- peer dependency and framework compatibility
- vulnerability audit evidence
- transitive risk for auth, security, payments, database, AI SDK, and deployment dependencies
- stack currency evidence for Node/TypeScript, frontend framework, Python/FastAPI, AI SDK, auth/security, database/ORM, and deployment runtime packs where detected
- upgrade or migration notes for high-impact packages

## Blocking Rule

For VibOS Comp, dependency decisions block completion if they rely on stale model memory, lack current source evidence for high-impact packages, use floating app versions without lockfile discipline, fail vulnerability audits, or have unresolved runtime/peer compatibility conflicts.
